<title>Science Against Evolution Wins StudyWeb Award</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFCC99">
<table bgcolor="PURPLE" width="100%,"><tbody><tr><td align="RIGHT">
<font color="WHITE">Blowing Our Own Horn - August 1999</font></td></tr></tbody></table>
<h1><center>Science Against Evolution Wins Web Site Award</center></h1>
<p>
<table cellpadding="10"><tbody><tr><td>
<!-- Start StudyWebTM Award Logo Link -->
<a data-original-url="http://www.studyweb.com" data-wayback-date="19981212" href="https://web.archive.org/web/19981212033115/http://www.studyweb.com">
<img alt="StudyWeb Award" border="0" src="http://www.studyweb.com/images/sw_award.gif"/></a>
<!-- End StudyWebTM Award Logo Link -->
</td>
<td>

We are pleased to announce that the Science Against Evolution web site recently won a StudyWebTM Academic Excellence award.

</td></tr></tbody></table>
</p><p>Unlike automated search engines that merely look for web pages containing a word or two of your choice, StudyWeb (<a data-original-url="http://www.studyweb.com" data-wayback-date="19981212" href="https://web.archive.org/web/19981212033115/http://www.studyweb.com">www.studyweb.com</a>) has a staff of nearly 200 researchers who evaluate web pages.  Web pages that are judged to be "research quality" are entered into their hierarchy of educational categories that range from Agriculture to Writing.  The Science category is the top of a hierarchy that includes the subheading Biology.  Under Biology is General Biology, which includes a section of Creation vs. Evolution.  A link to the archive of past Science Against Evolution Newsletters has been included in the Creation vs. Evolution section.



</p><p><table border="" width="100%">
